HEADWORD: borsh
<hw>borsh</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Yiddish <ets>borscht</ets>, fr.
Russian]</ety> <def>a Russian soup usually containing beet juice as a
foundation, and often served with sour cream. Also, as used in the U.S.,
a sour cabbage soup, called in Russian
<altname>shchi</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> borsch, borscht, borsht, borshch, bortsch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

